<!-- MAIN SECTION II: HORIZONTAL AXIS -->
<div class="section" id="horizontal-axis-main">
<p>The horizontal axis tracks <strong>WHERE you are in the narrative</strong>. Multiple measurement systems operate simultaneously — use whichever provides the clearest orientation for your current analysis.</p>
<div class="callout-info">
<h4>Key Principle:</h4>
<p>All horizontal measurement systems map onto each other. You can use <strong>clock positions</strong>, <strong>act structure</strong>, <strong>timestamps</strong>, <strong>beat markers</strong>, or <strong>symmetry points</strong> — they're different ways of measuring the same journey.</p>
<p style="margin-top: 12px;">Choose the system that gives you the clearest sense of position for your current analysis task.</p>
</div>
<!-- PART A -->
<div id="primary-measurement-systems">
<h3>A. Primary Measurement Systems</h3>
<!-- CLOCK POSITION -->
<h4>Clock Position (12-Point Circle)</h4>
<p><strong>Concept:</strong> The story as a complete circle, <code>12:00 → 12:00</code>, with the hero returning transformed.</p>
<div class="dimension-horizontal">
<h4>Key Clock Positions:</h4>
<ul>
<li><code>12:00</code> — Origin/Return point (Status Quo → New Equilibrium)</li>
<li><code>1:00-2:00</code> — Need becomes conscious, call to adventure</li>
<li><code>2:00-3:00</code></li>
<li><code>3:00</code> — Threshold/Go Point (crossing into new world)</li>
<li><code>3:00-4:00</code></li>
<li><code>4:00-5:00</code> — Search, trials, wanderer phase</li>
<li><code>5:00-6:00</code></li>
<li><code>6:00</code> — Midpoint/Find Point (revelation, meet the goddess)</li>
<li><code>6:00-7:00</code></li>
<li><code>7:00-8:00</code> — Take, warrior phase, attempts control</li>
<li><code>8:00-9:00</code></li>
<li><code>9:00</code> — Crisis/Death/Return begins</li>
<li><code>9:00-10:00</code></li>
<li><code>10:00-11:00</code> — Integration, final preparation</li>
<li><code>11:00-12:00</code></li>
<li><code>12:00</code> — Resolution, change embodied</li>
</ul>
</div>
<h4>Mirroring Axes:</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Vertical line <code>12:00 ↔ 6:00</code></strong> — Origin/return mirrors revelation</li>
<li><strong>Horizontal line <code>3:00 ↔ 9:00</code></strong> — Threshold mirrors crisis</li>
<li><code>2:00 ↔ 10:00</code> — Call mirrors return with knowledge</li>
<li><code>4:00 ↔ 8:00</code> — Descent mirrors ascent</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Use when:</strong> Tracking character transformation, identifying symmetrical story beats, analyzing cyclical narrative structure.</p>
<p><strong>→ Universal Structure doc:</strong> Complete clock system details, beat-by-beat breakdown</p>
<hr/>
<!-- WHICH FRAMEWORKS AT WHICH POSITION -->
<h4>Which Frameworks Are Most Relevant at Which Position</h4>
<p>Different story positions activate different frameworks. This is your quick reference for which analytical tools are most powerful at each coordinate:</p>
<p><strong><code>12:00</code> — Origin/Return</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Status quo analysis: World-building frameworks</li>
<li>Character baseline: <a class="cross-link" href="#">Jungian typing</a>, <a class="cross-link" href="#">Enneagram</a> assessment</li>
<li>Before/after comparison: Arc analysis tools</li>
<li><em>→ Most relevant: Establishment frameworks, comparison tools</em></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><code>1:00-2:00</code> — Need/Call</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Inciting incident: <a class="cross-link" href="#">Harmon</a> (NEED), <a class="cross-link" href="#">Truby</a> (catalyst)</li>
<li>Three goals: <a class="cross-link" href="#">McKee</a>, <a class="cross-link" href="#">Truby</a> (moral argument setup)</li>
<li>Character typing: <a class="cross-link" href="#">Enneagram</a>, <a class="cross-link" href="#">Jung</a> (baseline archetype)</li>
<li><em>→ Most relevant: Setup/catalyst frameworks</em></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><code>3:00</code> — Threshold</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Commitment: <a class="cross-link" href="#">Campbell</a> (crossing), <a class="cross-link" href="#">Dramatica</a> (go point)</li>
<li>World transition: <a class="cross-link" href="#">Harmon</a> (GO), <a class="cross-link" href="#">Hero's Journey</a></li>
<li>Genre conventions: Genre-specific threshold beats</li>
<li><em>→ Most relevant: Transition/commitment frameworks</em></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><code>6:00</code> — Midpoint</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Revelation: All midpoint beat systems</li>
<li>False victory/defeat: <a class="cross-link" href="#">Save the Cat</a>, <a class="cross-link" href="#">Blake Snyder</a></li>
<li>Meet the Goddess: <a class="cross-link" href="#">Campbell</a>, <a class="cross-link" href="#">Vogler</a></li>
<li>Vulnerability: Psychological analysis tools</li>
<li><em>→ Most relevant: Revelation/turning-point frameworks</em></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><code>9:00</code> — Crisis</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>All is Lost: <a class="cross-link" href="#">Save the Cat</a>, <a class="cross-link" href="#">Story Grid</a></li>
<li>Dark Night: Multiple beat systems</li>
<li>Death/Rebirth: <a class="cross-link" href="#">Campbell</a>, mythic analysis</li>
<li>Sacrifice: <a class="cross-link" href="#">Moral Premise</a>, thematic tools</li>
<li><em>→ Most relevant: Crisis/transformation frameworks</em></li>
</ul>
<hr/>
<!-- ACT STRUCTURE -->
<h4>Multiple Act Structures</h4>
<p>All act structures map onto the clock system. Use both simultaneously for maximum precision.</p>
<p><strong>Traditional 3-Act:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Act I</strong> (Setup) — <code>12:00</code> to <code>3:00</code></li>
<li><strong>Act II</strong> (Confrontation) — <code>3:00</code> to <code>9:00</code>
<ul>
<li>IIa: <code>3:00</code> to <code>6:00</code> (reaction, rising action)</li>
<li>IIb: <code>6:00</code> to <code>9:00</code> (proaction, complications)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Act III</strong> (Resolution) — <code>9:00</code> to <code>12:00</code></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>4-Act Structure (Scheer):</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Act 1</strong> (Orphan) — <code>12:00</code> to <code>3:00</code></li>
<li><strong>Act 2</strong> (Wanderer) — <code>3:00</code> to <code>6:00</code></li>
<li><strong>Act 3</strong> (Warrior) — <code>6:00</code> to <code>9:00</code></li>
<li><strong>Act 4</strong> (Martyr) — <code>9:00</code> to <code>12:00</code></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>5-Act Structure (Classical):</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Exposition → Rising Action → Climax → Falling Action → Denouement</li>
<li>Maps to: <code>12:00-2:00</code> → <code>2:00-6:00</code> → <code>6:00-7:00</code> → <code>7:00-10:00</code> → <code>10:00-12:00</code></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Use when:</strong> Following traditional screenplay structure, tracking pacing, identifying conventional beats.</p>
<p><strong>Cross-system alignment:</strong> All act structures map onto the clock — use both systems simultaneously for maximum precision.</p>
<hr/>
<!-- RUNTIME/TIMESTAMPS -->
<h4>Runtime/Timestamps/Page Number</h4>
<p><strong>Absolute Time Measurement:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Actual minutes:seconds from film start</li>
<li><strong>Format:</strong> <code>00:00:00</code> to [runtime]</li>
<li>Most concrete, verifiable position system</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Percentage-Based:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>0% to 100% of total runtime</li>
<li>Allows comparison between different length films</li>
<li>Standard beats often occur at predictable percentages:
                        <ul>
<li>12.5% — Inciting incident zone</li>
<li>25% — End of Act I/Threshold</li>
<li>50% — Midpoint</li>
<li>75% — Crisis zone</li>
<li>87.5% — Climax approach</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Use when:</strong> Logging actual scenes, comparing films of different lengths, tracking precise visual/audio moments.</p>
<div class="callout-example">
<h4>Logging Format Example:</h4>
<p><code>[00:47:23] / Psychological Dimension 2 / 6:00</code></p>
<p>Character discovers truth about identity</p>
<p style="margin-top: 8px;">→ Meet the Goddess beat</p>
<p>• Jung: Shadow revelation</p>
</div>
<hr/>
<!-- BEAT MARKERS -->
<h4>Beat Markers (Structural Beats)</h4>
<p><strong>Major Story Beats</strong> applicable across most narratives:</p>
<p><strong>Setup Phase:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Opening Image <code>12:00</code></li>
<li>Theme Stated</li>
<li>Setup/Status Quo established</li>
<li>Catalyst/Inciting Incident <code>1:00</code> zone</li>
<li>Debate/Refusal <code>2:00</code> zone</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Threshold <code>3:00</code></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Break into Two</li>
<li>Go Point</li>
<li>B Story begins</li>
<li>Promise of the Premise</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Rising Phase:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Fun and Games <code>4:00-5:00</code></li>
<li>First Pinch Point</li>
<li>Complications build</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Midpoint <code>6:00</code></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>False Victory or False Defeat</li>
<li>Stakes raised</li>
<li>Ticking Clock</li>
<li>A Story/B Story merge</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Descending/Warrior Phase:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Bad Guys Close In <code>7:00</code></li>
<li>Second Pinch Point</li>
<li>All Is Lost <code>8:00</code></li>
<li>Dark Night of the Soul <code>8:30</code></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Crisis <code>9:00</code></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Break into Three</li>
<li>Sacrifice/Death moment</li>
<li>Transformation trigger</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Resolution Phase:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Finale begins <code>9:30-11:00</code></li>
<li>Execute New Plan</li>
<li>High Tower Surprise</li>
<li>Dig Deep Down</li>
<li>Execution of Solution</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Resolution <code>12:00</code></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Final Image</li>
<li>New Status Quo</li>
<li>Character changed/world changed</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Use when:</strong> Tracking plot mechanics, identifying missing beats, comparing against proven structure.</p>
<p><strong>→ Multiple beat systems exist:</strong> <a class="cross-link" href="#">Save the Cat</a>, <a class="cross-link" href="#">Story Grid</a>, and others — all map onto clock positions.</p>
<hr/>
<!-- SYMMETRY POINTS -->
<h4>Symmetry Points &amp; Mirroring</h4>
<p><strong>Concept:</strong> Narrative elements echo across axes, creating geometric meaning through repetition and variation.</p>
<p><strong>Primary Symmetry Axes:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Vertical Axis <code>12-6</code> line:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Beginning mirrors ending <code>12:00 ↔ 12:00</code></li>
<li>Call mirrors return <code>2:00 ↔ 10:00</code></li>
<li>Threshold mirrors crisis <code>3:00 ↔ 9:00</code></li>
<li>Descent mirrors ascent <code>4:00 ↔ 8:00</code></li>
<li>Lower world peak mirrors itself <code>6:00</code> = center</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Horizontal Axis <code>9-3</code> line:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Upper world (conscious, order, status quo)</li>
<li>Lower world (unconscious, chaos, transformation)</li>
<li>Dividing line between ordinary and special world</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Cross-Mirroring (Diagonal):</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>1:00 ↔ 7:00</code> — Need mirrors price</li>
<li><code>2:00 ↔ 8:00</code> — Call mirrors dark night</li>
<li><code>4:00 ↔ 10:00</code> — Trial mirrors triumph</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Shadow Mirroring:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Light action (first half) performed as dark action (second half)</li>
<li>"Good" choice early becomes "corrupted" choice later</li>
<li>Character's beginning strength becomes ending weakness</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Thematic Inversion:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Scene/image from <code>2:00</code> repeated at <code>10:00</code> with opposite meaning</li>
<li>Same dialogue/visual with character transformed</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Use when:</strong> Identifying deeper structure, tracking motif development, analyzing directorial intent, finding missing symmetrical beats.</p>
<div class="callout-info">
<h4>Analysis Protocol:</h4>
<ol>
<li>Identify key moment at position X</li>
<li>Check mirror position across relevant axis</li>
<li>Examine: repetition, variation, inversion, or absence</li>
<li>Analyze what the comparison reveals</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<!-- PART B -->
<div id="key-story-positions">
<h3>B. Key Story Position Coordinates (Horizontal Markers)</h3>
<p>Each major position has characteristic functions across all dimensions. These are <strong>position signatures</strong> — what tends to happen here.</p>
<!-- 12:00 ORIGIN/RETURN -->
<h4><code>12:00</code> — ORIGIN/RETURN</h4>
<p><strong>Position Character:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Beginning:</strong> Status quo, ordinary world, hero's starting point</li>
<li><strong>Ending:</strong> New equilibrium, resolution, changed world/changed hero</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Story Depth Cross-Dimension Signature:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Surface Dimension 5:</strong> Visual establishment/final image</li>
<li><strong>Structural Dimension 4:</strong> Story world rules/new rules</li>
<li><strong>Psychological Dimension 2:</strong> Character baseline/transformed character</li>
<li><strong>Cognitive Dimension 3:</strong> Initial worldview/changed belief system</li>
<li><strong>Archetype Dimension 1:</strong> Orphan archetype/Master archetype</li>
<li><strong>Core Dimension 0:</strong> Problem stated/problem resolved</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What to Examine:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><em>Beginning:</em> What world are we in? Who is the hero before change?</li>
<li><em>Ending:</em> How has the world changed? Who is the hero after change?</li>
<li><em>Comparison:</em> What is the same/different between beginning and ending <code>12:00</code>?</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Mirroring:</strong> This position mirrors itself — comparison reveals the arc's total movement.</p>
<p><strong>Common Beats:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Opening image</li>
<li>Final image</li>
<li>"Before" snapshot</li>
<li>"After" snapshot</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>↔ Related Coordinates:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>12:00 / Psychological Dimension 2</code> → Character baseline psychology</li>
<li><code>12:00 / Core Dimension 0</code> → Core problem introduction/resolution</li>
<li><code>6:00 / all dimensions</code> → Midpoint provides contrast</li>
</ul>
<hr/>
<!-- 1:00-2:00 NEED/CALL ZONE -->
<h4><code>1:00-2:00</code> — NEED/CALL ZONE</h4>
<p><strong>Position Character:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Need becomes conscious</li>
<li>Inciting incident</li>
<li>Call to adventure</li>
<li>Refusal/debate</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Story Depth Cross-Dimension Signature:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Surface Dimension 5:</strong> Disruption of normalcy (visual, event)</li>
<li><strong>Structural Dimension 4:</strong> Story question posed, central conflict introduced</li>
<li><strong>Psychological Dimension 2:</strong> Internal need vs external want clarified</li>
<li><strong>Cognitive Dimension 3:</strong> Current belief system challenged</li>
<li><strong>Archetype Dimension 1:</strong> Orphan realizes incompleteness</li>
<li><strong>Core Dimension 0:</strong> Thematic tension introduced</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What to Examine:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>What disrupts the status quo?</li>
<li>What does the hero need (vs what they want)?</li>
<li>What is the refusal/hesitation?</li>
<li>What are the three goals? (physical, emotional, spiritual)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Mirroring:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>2:00 ↔ 10:00</code> — Call mirrors return with knowledge</li>
<li><code>1:00 ↔ 11:00</code> — Need mirrors fulfillment</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Common Beats:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Catalyst</li>
<li>Herald appears</li>
<li>Inciting incident</li>
<li>Refusal of the call</li>
</ul>
<hr/>
<!-- 3:00 THRESHOLD/GO POINT -->
<h4><code>3:00</code> — THRESHOLD/GO POINT</h4>
<p><strong>Position Character:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Point of no return</li>
<li>Crossing into special world</li>
<li>Break into Act II</li>
<li>Commitment to journey</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Story Depth Cross-Dimension Signature:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Surface Dimension 5:</strong> Visual transition, crossing literal threshold</li>
<li><strong>Structural Dimension 4:</strong> Story structure shifts, rules change</li>
<li><strong>Psychological Dimension 2:</strong> Ego death begins, identity destabilizes</li>
<li><strong>Cognitive Dimension 3:</strong> Old thinking patterns become insufficient</li>
<li><strong>Archetype Dimension 1:</strong> Orphan → Wanderer transition</li>
<li><strong>Core Dimension 0:</strong> Central question formally asked</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What to Examine:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>What is left behind?</li>
<li>What is the literal/metaphorical threshold?</li>
<li>What pulls/pushes hero across?</li>
<li>What changes after this point?</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Mirroring:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>3:00 ↔ 9:00</code> — Threshold mirrors crisis/return threshold</li>
<li><strong>Horizontal axis:</strong> Above line (order) → below line (chaos)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Common Beats:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Crossing the first threshold</li>
<li>Meeting threshold guardian</li>
<li>Break into Two</li>
<li>Go Point</li>
</ul>
<div class="callout-warning">
<h4>Critical:</h4>
<p>This is where "the story begins to be about what it's about."</p>
</div>
<hr/>
<!-- 6:00 MIDPOINT -->
<h4><code>6:00</code> — MIDPOINT/FIND POINT/REVELATION</h4>
<p><strong>Position Character:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Story center</li>
<li>Major revelation</li>
<li>Find what was sought</li>
<li>Maximum vulnerability</li>
<li>Temptation to stay</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Story Depth Cross-Dimension Signature:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Surface Dimension 5:</strong> Major visual/plot reveal</li>
<li><strong>Structural Dimension 4:</strong> Stakes shift, ticking clock, false victory/defeat</li>
<li><strong>Psychological Dimension 2:</strong> Meet the Goddess, need fulfilled, intimacy/truth</li>
<li><strong>Cognitive Dimension 3:</strong> Core belief confronted directly</li>
<li><strong>Archetype Dimension 1:</strong> Wanderer → Warrior transition begins</li>
<li><strong>Core Dimension 0:</strong> Thematic truth exposed</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What to Examine:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>What is discovered/revealed?</li>
<li>What does the hero find that they were seeking?</li>
<li>Why can't they stay here?</li>
<li>What forces them to continue?</li>
<li>What vulnerability is exposed?</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Mirroring:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>6:00</code> mirrors itself (center point)</li>
<li><strong>Horizontal axis:</strong> <code>12:00 ↔ 6:00</code> (status quo vs revelation)</li>
<li>Creates symmetry for entire structure</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Common Beats:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Midpoint</li>
<li>Meet the Goddess</li>
<li>Find Point</li>
<li>Major revelation</li>
<li>False victory</li>
<li>False defeat</li>
</ul>
<div class="callout-info">
<h4>Transition Point:</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Left side</strong> = Circumstance (dragged by events)</li>
<li><strong>Right side</strong> = Agency (fighting back with new tools)</li>
</ul>
<p style="margin-top: 12px;"><strong>Critical:</strong> After this point, ambiguity ends — sides are chosen.</p>
</div>
<hr/>
<!-- 9:00 CRISIS/DEATH/RETURN -->
<h4><code>9:00</code> — CRISIS/DEATH/RETURN</h4>
<p><strong>Position Character:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Lowest point</li>
<li>Ego death</li>
<li>Sacrifice required</li>
<li>Transformation triggered</li>
<li>Return begins</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Story Depth Cross-Dimension Signature:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Surface Dimension 5:</strong> Visual darkness, loss, defeat<br/><em>→ Frameworks: Semiotic codes (Barthes), visual symbolism</em></li>
<li><strong>Structural Dimension 4:</strong> All Is Lost beat, Dark Night of Soul<br/><em>→ Frameworks: Save the Cat (Blake Snyder), Story Grid (Coyne)</em></li>
<li><strong>Psychological Dimension 2:</strong> Psychological breakdown, false self dies<br/><em>→ Frameworks: Jung (ego death), Enneagram (disintegration)</em></li>
<li><strong>Cognitive Dimension 3:</strong> Thought patterns shattered, worldview collapses<br/><em>→ Frameworks: Cognitive dissonance theory, belief revision</em></li>
<li><strong>Archetype Dimension 1:</strong> Warrior → Martyr transition<br/><em>→ Frameworks: Campbell (ordeal), Vogler (resurrection)</em></li>
<li><strong>Core Dimension 0:</strong> Price paid for ignoring thematic truth<br/><em>→ Frameworks: Moral Premise (Williams), Truby (self-revelation)</em></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What to Examine:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>What dies? (literally or metaphorically)</li>
<li>What is sacrificed?</li>
<li>What is the cost of the journey?</li>
<li>What messenger/mentor sacrifice occurs?</li>
<li>What triggers the return/rebirth?</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Mirroring:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>9:00 ↔ 3:00</code> — Crisis mirrors threshold</li>
<li><strong>Horizontal axis:</strong> Below line (chaos) → above line (order)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Common Beats:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>All Is Lost</li>
<li>Dark Night of the Soul</li>
<li>Whiff of Death</li>
<li>Break into Three</li>
<li>Meeting with Death/Mentor sacrifice</li>
</ul>
<div class="callout-warning">
<h4>Transition Point:</h4>
<p>This is the "payment" for crossing at <code>3:00</code>. Hero proved worthy/good. Resurrection/rebirth moment.</p>
<p style="margin-top: 12px;"><strong>Critical:</strong> Hero nearly dies, dies symbolically, or witnesses death.</p>
</div>
</div>
<!-- PART C -->
<div id="horizontal-movement-patterns">
<h3>C. Horizontal Movement Patterns</h3>
<p>Understanding how to move along the horizontal axis — tracking elements across story time.</p>
<hr/>
<!-- LINEAR PROGRESSION -->
<h4>Linear Progression <code>12:00 → 12:00</code></h4>
<p><strong>Simple Forward Movement:</strong> Follow the story chronologically, examining each coordinate in sequence.</p>
<div class="callout-info">
<h4>Protocol:</h4>
<ol>
<li>Establish position (clock/act/timestamp)</li>
<li>Identify which beat/function is occurring</li>
<li>Examine across selected dimensions</li>
<li>Document findings</li>
<li>Move to next position</li>
<li>Repeat</li>
</ol>
</div>
<p><strong>Use for:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>First-time analysis of unfamiliar film</li>
<li>Comprehensive structural breakdown</li>
<li>Teaching/demonstrating structure</li>
<li>Logging all scenes</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Variation — Skip Pattern:</strong> Jump by act or major beat rather than scene-by-scene:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>12:00 → 3:00 → 6:00 → 9:00 → 12:00</code> (major positions only)</li>
</ul>
<hr/>
<!-- MIRRORING ANALYSIS -->
<h4>Mirroring Analysis (Symmetry Tracking)</h4>
<p><strong>Vertical Axis Mirroring:</strong> Compare across the <code>12-6</code> line to find echoes, variations, inversions.</p>
<div class="callout-info">
<h4>Protocol:</h4>
<ol>
<li>Identify strong moment at position X</li>
<li>Calculate mirror position:
                            <ul>
<li>For <code>2:00</code>, mirror is <code>10:00</code></li>
<li>For <code>4:00</code>, mirror is <code>8:00</code></li>
<li>For <code>3:00</code>, mirror is <code>9:00</code></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Navigate to mirror position</li>
<li>Examine: repetition, variation, inversion, absence</li>
<li>Analyze what the comparison reveals</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="callout-example">
<h4>Example Analysis:</h4>
<ul>
<li><code>2:00 / Surface Dimension 5</code>: Hero refuses call, stays in comfort</li>
<li><code>10:00 / Surface Dimension 5</code>: Hero embraces mission, acts with courage</li>
<li><strong>Mirroring reveals:</strong> Character transformation via inverted choice</li>
</ul>
</div>
<p><strong>Harmonic vs Shadow Mirroring:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Harmonic:</strong> Same action, successful on return</li>
<li><strong>Shadow:</strong> "Good" action becomes "dark" version on return</li>
</ul>
<hr/>
<!-- CYCLICAL/SPIRAL RETURNS -->
<h4>Cyclical/Spiral Returns</h4>
<p><strong>Non-Linear Repetition:</strong> Story returns to similar positions/situations but at different knowledge levels.</p>
<p><strong>Pattern Recognition:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Same location revisited</li>
<li>Same dialogue repeated with new meaning</li>
<li>Same choice offered again</li>
<li>Same test repeated</li>
</ul>
<div class="callout-info">
<h4>Analysis Protocol:</h4>
<ol>
<li>Identify first occurrence (Position A)</li>
<li>Identify return occurrence (Position B)</li>
<li>Measure: time elapsed, character change, stakes shift</li>
<li>Examine what the repetition reveals</li>
</ol>
</div>
<p><strong>Common Cycles:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Opening location → closing location (same place, different person)</li>
<li>Repeated character test (fails → succeeds)</li>
<li>Recurring symbol/image with evolving meaning</li>
</ul>
<hr/>
<!-- PARALLEL TIMELINE TRACKING -->
<h4>Parallel Timeline Tracking</h4>
<p><strong>Multiple Simultaneous Progressions:</strong> Some films run multiple characters through similar coordinates simultaneously or in alternation.</p>
<p><strong>Types:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ensemble:</strong> Multiple heroes at different positions</li>
<li><strong>A/B Story:</strong> Protagonist + subplot character journeys</li>
<li><strong>Parallel Worlds:</strong> Dual realities at same timestamp</li>
<li><strong>Temporal:</strong> Past/present/future simultaneous</li>
</ul>
<div class="callout-info">
<h4>Analysis Protocol:</h4>
<ol>
<li>Identify separate timeline threads</li>
<li>Track each thread's position independently</li>
<li>Note intersection points</li>
<li>Analyze: contrast, complement, collision, convergence</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="callout-example">
<h4>Notation Example:</h4>
<p><code>[Timestamp] / [Story Timeline Position] / [Story Depth Dimension]</code></p>
<p style="margin-top: 12px;">• Thread A: Character 1 at <code>6:00</code></p>
<p>• Thread B: Character 2 at <code>3:00</code></p>
<p>• Intersection: Threads converge at <code>9:00</code></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
